The paper proposes a distributed scenario-based chance-constrained optimization formulation for outage scheduling, which involves using machine learning to build a proxy for predicting outcomes of power system operation processes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with power system operation processes, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a solution for minimizing operation-cost expectation while satisfying reliability-related constraints, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
